<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12053&amp;p=137169#p137169</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12053&amp;p=137169#p137169"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Graphics - Tools]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12053&amp;p=137169#p137169"><![CDATA[
YY-CHR prefers images use 256-color palettes, even if you're only using 16 colors in the image.<br /><br />There's also the option of copying the data from the clipboard to YY-CHR's 8bpp Bitmap tab (if you're using YY-CHR.NET, anyways), but you'll still need to have the image use a 256 color palette.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5692">freem</a> — Mon Dec 01, 2014 1:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
